#gwas_lmm_demo <- function(){
  library(lme4)
  source("lmm_eigen.r")
  source("gen_sim.r")
  
  #Simulate genotype data
  data = gen_sim(m = 1000, k = 4, n = 300, Ns = 100, Nc = 100, d = c(1.4,1.2,1,0.7), Vg = 2, Ve = 4 , Vs = 40 )
  #detach(data)
  attach(data)
## The following objects are masked from data (pos = 5):
## 
##     beta, d, geno, group, k, m, n, SNPc, SNPs, y, yc, yz, Z
  layout(matrix(1:3))
  hist(y, main="observed phenotype")
  hist(yz, main="ancestry-associated effect"); 
  hist(yc, main="additive genetic effect"); 

  #Standard deviation of the genetic component
  print(sd(yc));
## [1] 7.973732
  #Standard deviation of the ancestry component
  print(sd(yz))
## [1] 5.479509
  readline(prompt="Press [enter] to continue")
## [1] ""
  #Demonstrate population structure
  m.g=svd(geno)
  PC.svd =  m.g$u %*% diag(m.g$d)  
  layout(matrix(1))
  plot(PC.svd[,1:2], main="Population structure",cex.main=.8)
  points(PC.svd[group==1,1:2],col="blue")
  points(PC.svd[group==2,1:2],col="red")
  points(PC.svd[group==3,1:2],col="green")
  points(PC.svd[group==4,1:2],col="purple")

  readline(prompt="Press [enter] to continue")
## [1] ""
  #Run a GWAS 
  GWAS=matrix(nrow = m,ncol = 3)
  for(i in 1:m){
    GWAS[i,]=coef(summary(lm(y ~ geno[,i])))[2,-3]
  }
  
  #genomic inflation
  chisq  = qchisq(GWAS[,3],1,lower.tail=FALSE)
  (lambda = median(chisq)/qchisq(.5,1,lower.tail=FALSE))
## [1] 1.491157
  #qq plot
  qqplot(y= -log10(GWAS[,3]),x=-log10(runif(m)) )
  abline(a=0,b=1)
  usr <- par( "usr" )
  text(x = usr[2]-1,usr[3]+2,labels = sprintf("Inflation lambda=%1.2f",lambda))

  readline(prompt="Press [enter] to continue")
## [1] ""
  #Manhattan plot, structural and causal SNPs highlighted in red and blue  
  plot(-log10(GWAS[,3]),main = "Manhattan plot of GWAS without correction for pop structure",cex.main=.8)
  points(SNPc,-log10(GWAS[SNPc,3]),col="blue")
  points(SNPs,-log10(GWAS[SNPs,3]),col="red")
  abline(h=-log10(0.05/m),lty=2)
  legend(x="topright",legend = c("Ancestry SNP","Causal SNP"),col=c("red","blue"),pch=c(1,1))

  readline(prompt="Press [enter] to continue")
## [1] ""
  #Genetic relatedness matrix (correlation)
  sgeno = scale(geno)
  GRM   = sgeno %*% t(sgeno) / (n*k-1)               #Covariance
  GRMs  = sgeno[,SNPs] %*% t(sgeno[,SNPs]) / (n*k-1) #Correlation

  image(GRMs,main="Relatedness matrix",col=rev(rainbow(5)))

  #Ancestry informative PCs
  Ry.pc=cor(y,PC.svd)
  Ryz.pc=cor(yz,PC.svd)
  print(abs(Ryz.pc[1:10]))
##  [1] 0.456186488 0.733066875 0.031060892 0.017424447 0.029874123
##  [6] 0.027387730 0.022058842 0.013972981 0.039877699 0.004998946
  print(abs(Ry.pc[1:10]))
##  [1] 0.212332044 0.410389348 0.012689888 0.001187759 0.014762722
##  [6] 0.039932779 0.014737360 0.010697335 0.070908014 0.028908217
  readline(prompt="Press [enter] to continue")
## [1] ""
  #Run a GWAS conditionining on PC
  GWAS.pca=matrix(nrow = m,ncol = 3)
  for(i in 1:m){
    GWAS.pca[i,]=coef(summary(lm(y ~ geno[,i] + PC.svd[,1:3])))[2,-3]
  }
  
  #genomic inflation
  chisq  = qchisq(GWAS.pca[,3],1,lower.tail=FALSE)
  (lambda = median(chisq)/qchisq(.5,1,lower.tail=FALSE))
## [1] 1.215386
  #qq plot
  qqplot(y= -log10(GWAS.pca[,3]),x=-log10(runif(m)),main = "GWAS corrected for ancestry informative PCs",cex.main=.8)
  abline(a=0,b=1)
  usr <- par( "usr" )
  text(x = usr[2]-1,usr[3]+2,labels = sprintf("Inflation lambda=%1.2f",lambda))

  readline(prompt="Press [enter] to continue")
## [1] ""
  #Manhattan, structural and causal SNPs highlighted in red and blue  
  plot(-log10(GWAS.pca[,3]),main = "Manhattan plot for GWAS corrected for ancestry informative PCs",cex.main=.8)
  points(SNPc,-log10(GWAS.pca[SNPc,3]),col="blue")
  points(SNPs,-log10(GWAS.pca[SNPs,3]),col="red")
  abline(h=-log10(0.05/m),lty=2)
  legend(x="topright",legend = c("Ancestry SNP","Causal SNP"),col=c("red","blue"),pch=c(1,1))

  readline(prompt="Press [enter] to continue")
## [1] ""
  #GWAS P-values for the ancestry informative SNPs before and after correction for PC
  print(quantile(GWAS.pca[SNPs,3]))
##         0%        25%        50%        75%       100% 
## 0.01418306 0.20634166 0.52267158 0.79860874 0.99417437
  print(quantile(GWAS[SNPs,3]))
##           0%          25%          50%          75%         100% 
## 3.697590e-11 2.664707e-05 1.144227e-03 4.517330e-02 9.902707e-01
  #############################################################
  # Compare effect estimates and P values of the ancestry informative SNP 
  # FP associations
  #############################################################
  idx_s=which.min(GWAS[SNPs,3])
  C = SNPs[idx_s]
  print("lm (y ~ geno[,C]  )");
## [1] "lm (y ~ geno[,C]  )"
  print(coef(summary(lm (y ~ geno[,C]  ))))
##              Estimate Std. Error   t value     Pr(>|t|)
## (Intercept)  1.488325  0.5063784  2.939155 3.354173e-03
## geno[, C]   -2.541171  0.3805278 -6.678017 3.697590e-11
  print("lm (y ~ geno[,C] + as.factor(group) )");
## [1] "lm (y ~ geno[,C] + as.factor(group) )"
  print(coef(summary(lm (y ~ geno[,C] + as.factor(group) )))[1:2,])
##               Estimate Std. Error    t value     Pr(>|t|)
## (Intercept) -7.2967833  0.6856313 -10.642430 2.472191e-25
## geno[, C]   -0.3571145  0.3439660  -1.038226 2.993749e-01
  print("lm (y ~ geno[,C] + PC.svd[,1:3] )");
## [1] "lm (y ~ geno[,C] + PC.svd[,1:3] )"
  print(coef(summary(lm (y ~ geno[,C] + PC.svd[,1:3] )))[1:2,])
##               Estimate Std. Error    t value  Pr(>|t|)
## (Intercept)  4.3437598  6.8050708  0.6383122 0.5233928
## geno[, C]   -0.4618721  0.3891204 -1.1869643 0.2354776
  print("lmer (y ~ 1 + geno[,C] + (1|group) )");
## [1] "lmer (y ~ 1 + geno[,C] + (1|group) )"
  print(coef(summary(lmer (y ~ 1 + geno[,C] + (1|group) )))[1:2,])
##               Estimate Std. Error    t value
## (Intercept) -0.9113159  3.1934228 -0.2853728
## geno[, C]   -0.3711871  0.3438233 -1.0795870
  print("lmm.svd(y,  geno[,C, drop = F], sgeno )");
## [1] "lmm.svd(y,  geno[,C, drop = F], sgeno )"
  print(coef(summary(lmm.svd(y,  geno[,C, drop = F], sgeno ) )))
##                  Estimate   Std. Error   t value   Pr(>|t|)
## XrIntercept  3.750051e+11 2.585515e+11  1.450408 0.14725908
## XrX         -3.191429e-03 1.900935e-03 -1.678873 0.09348981
  print("lmm.eig(y,  geno[,C, drop = F], GRM )");
## [1] "lmm.eig(y,  geno[,C, drop = F], GRM )"
  print(coef(summary(lmm.eig(y,  geno[,C, drop = F], GRM))))
##                  Estimate   Std. Error       t value  Pr(>|t|)
## XrIntercept  1.105833e+00 4.745304e-09  2.330374e+08 0.0000000
## XrX         -4.300100e-15 2.116924e-09 -2.031296e-06 0.9999984
  print("lmm.chl(y,  geno[,C, drop = F], GRM )");
## [1] "lmm.chl(y,  geno[,C, drop = F], GRM )"
  print(coef(summary(lmm.chl(y,  geno[,C, drop = F], GRM))))
##                  Estimate   Std. Error       t value Pr(>|t|)
## XrIntercept  1.105833e+00 1.716183e-07  6.443562e+06 0.000000
## XrX         -6.208366e-12 7.990474e-08 -7.769709e-05 0.999938
  #It will work with the standardized genotypes
  print("lmm.eig(y,  geno[,C, drop = F], GRMs )");
## [1] "lmm.eig(y,  geno[,C, drop = F], GRMs )"
  print(coef(summary(lmm.eig(y,  geno[,C, drop = F], GRMs))))
##                  Estimate   Std. Error       t value  Pr(>|t|)
## XrIntercept  1.105833e+00 4.024269e-09  2.747911e+08 0.0000000
## XrX         -2.433395e-16 4.584319e-10 -5.308083e-07 0.9999996
  print("lmm.chl(y,  geno[,C, drop = F], GRMs )");
## [1] "lmm.chl(y,  geno[,C, drop = F], GRMs )"
  print(coef(summary(lmm.chl(y,  geno[,C, drop = F], GRMs))))
##                  Estimate   Std. Error       t value Pr(>|t|)
## XrIntercept  1.105833e+00 1.368252e-07  8.082089e+06 0.000000
## XrX         -2.930113e-13 1.559372e-08 -1.879034e-05 0.999985
  readline(prompt="Press [enter] to continue")
## [1] ""
  #############################################################
  # Compare effect estimates and P values of the causal SNP 
  # TP associations
  #############################################################
  idx_s=which.min(GWAS[SNPc,3])
  C = SNPc[idx_s]
  print("lm (y ~ geno[,C]  )");
## [1] "lm (y ~ geno[,C]  )"
  print(coef(summary(lm (y ~ geno[,C]  ))))
##              Estimate Std. Error    t value     Pr(>|t|)
## (Intercept)  2.187783  0.4262530   5.132591 3.331757e-07
## geno[, C]   -4.153337  0.3864396 -10.747698 8.715365e-26
  print("lm (y ~ geno[,C] + as.factor(group) )");
## [1] "lm (y ~ geno[,C] + as.factor(group) )"
  print(coef(summary(lm (y ~ geno[,C] + as.factor(group) )))[1:2,])
##              Estimate Std. Error    t value     Pr(>|t|)
## (Intercept) -4.301720  0.5323348  -8.080854 1.561878e-15
## geno[, C]   -3.869248  0.3166093 -12.220890 1.899439e-32
  print("lm (y ~ geno[,C] + PC.svd[,1:3] )");
## [1] "lm (y ~ geno[,C] + PC.svd[,1:3] )"
  print(coef(summary(lm (y ~ geno[,C] + PC.svd[,1:3] )))[1:2,])
##              Estimate Std. Error     t value     Pr(>|t|)
## (Intercept)  4.634250  6.4498805   0.7185016 4.725885e-01
## geno[, C]   -4.098001  0.3506496 -11.6868842 5.912619e-30
  print("lmer (y ~ 1 + geno[,C] + (1|group) )");
## [1] "lmer (y ~ 1 + geno[,C] + (1|group) )"
  print(coef(summary(lmer (y ~ 1 + geno[,C] + (1|group) )))[1:2,])
##              Estimate Std. Error     t value
## (Intercept)  1.948940  3.1695230   0.6149001
## geno[, C]   -3.870683  0.3166071 -12.2255093
  print("lmm.svd(y,  geno[,C, drop = F], sgeno )");
## [1] "lmm.svd(y,  geno[,C, drop = F], sgeno )"
  print(coef(summary(lmm.svd(y,  geno[,C, drop = F], sgeno ) )))
##                  Estimate   Std. Error   t value     Pr(>|t|)
## XrIntercept  3.692728e+11 2.418397e+11  1.526932 1.270948e-01
## XrX         -1.287179e-02 1.778066e-03 -7.239210 8.999357e-13
  print("lmm.eig(y,  geno[,C, drop = F], GRM )");
## [1] "lmm.eig(y,  geno[,C, drop = F], GRM )"
  print(coef(summary(lmm.eig(y,  geno[,C, drop = F], GRM))))
##                  Estimate   Std. Error       t value  Pr(>|t|)
## XrIntercept  8.450000e-01 4.544818e-09  1.859261e+08 0.0000000
## XrX         -1.895404e-14 2.027485e-09 -9.348545e-06 0.9999925
  print("lmm.chl(y,  geno[,C, drop = F], GRM )");
## [1] "lmm.chl(y,  geno[,C, drop = F], GRM )"
  print(coef(summary(lmm.chl(y,  geno[,C, drop = F], GRM))))
##                  Estimate   Std. Error       t value  Pr(>|t|)
## XrIntercept  8.450000e-01 1.643676e-07  5.140917e+06 0.0000000
## XrX         -2.687388e-11 7.652882e-08 -3.511603e-04 0.9997199
  #It will work with the standardized genotypes
  print("lmm.eig(y,  geno[,C, drop = F], GRMs )");
## [1] "lmm.eig(y,  geno[,C, drop = F], GRMs )"
  print(coef(summary(lmm.eig(y,  geno[,C, drop = F], GRMs))))
##                Estimate Std. Error   t value      Pr(>|t|)
## XrIntercept  0.81187731 0.01905943  42.59714 3.884752e-242
## XrX         -0.02517081 0.00217119 -11.59310  1.574295e-29
  print("lmm.chl(y,  geno[,C, drop = F], GRMs )");
## [1] "lmm.chl(y,  geno[,C, drop = F], GRMs )"
  print(coef(summary(lmm.chl(y,  geno[,C, drop = F], GRMs))))
##                Estimate  Std. Error   t value      Pr(>|t|)
## XrIntercept  0.81176246 0.019053310  42.60480 3.411931e-242
## XrX         -0.02514559 0.002171471 -11.57998  1.806645e-29
  #remove attached variables to environment
  detach(data)
#}
